article.headline: Radford 87, Campbell 80
article.story: RADFORD, Va. (AP) -- Chris Oliver had 28 points and 19 rebounds to lead Radford to a 87-80 win over Campbell on Saturday night in the school's home opener. The Highlanders (2-5) led by as many as 12 points in the first period and went into halftime up 46-36 in the first matchup between the teams since 1994. The Camels (3-1) crept back to within one three times in the second period and came to within 80-76 with a minute to play on a layup by Ledell Eackles. Oliver kept Radford alive, scoring a jumper and five free-throws in the remaining minute. Reggie McIntyre added 17 points and 10 rebounds and Amir Johnson had 14 for the Highlanders. Jonathan Rodriguez led Campbell with 25 points and 15 rebounds and Ruell Pringle added 23.
